---
/*
  DESIGN CONCEPT: "The Warm Hearth"

  Inspired by Dhamaka NYC's explosive monochrome-with-red-accent approach
  and the layered editorial typography of SŌM (Awwwards SOTD Jan 2026).

  The name "AVA MAE'S" appears in enormous ghosted serif type behind the
  hero pizza photo, creating a layered editorial composition where food
  and typography physically interlock. The pizza shot — prosciutto,
  arugula, shaved parm on a blistered crust — is the most striking image
  and becomes the visual anchor of the entire site.

  The palette is drawn from the interior of a wood-fired oven: deep
  charcoal, warm amber, cream linen. One accent color — a terracotta
  that references both brick ovens and Italian earth — provides all
  the visual heat the design needs.

  The menu section reads like an actual printed Italian menu: categories
  separated by thin rules, prices right-aligned, dot leaders connecting
  name to price. No cards, no grids, no template patterns.

  Signature moment: The hero composition. The name is so large it
  becomes architecture. The pizza photograph is composited into the
  type, creating something that looks more like a magazine cover than
  a restaurant website.
*/

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
